    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35c.16"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">SIOUX FALLS INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 1</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Sioux Falls, South Dakota
                        <lb/>
                    Washington Senior High School       Telephone 336-3684      315 South Main Avenue 57102
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>December 16, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Nebraska Press</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>901 North 17th St.</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68508</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Nr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Upon completion of a number of your works, I have discovered, and justifiably so, that I have become what you termed in your <hi rend="underline">Cycle of the West</hi> a "fan" of yours.</p>
                    
                <p>In consulting with the other members of my department, we concluded that a personal appearance on your part is very desirable.</p>
                
                <p>I am presently instructing in American History on the secondary level in Sioux Falls, <hi rend="caps">S.D.</hi> Our area of concern at the moment deals with the American Indian and his culture. I believe it most beneficial if you would generously grant us a personal appearance.</p>
                
                <p>I have been assured that you would speak a maximum of twice in a large group setting. A small group setting is also possible if desirable, although arrangements would differ. I must admit our resources are limited, but we would greatly appreciate y1our<sic>your</sic> presence.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute> 
                
                    <signed>Thomas R. Holmes</signed>
                    <signed>Thomas R. Holmes 
                    Department of Social Science</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
